A WOMAN from the Free State has survived a torturous ordeal after allegedly being repeatedly gang-raped on 28 January. As a result, cops have launched a manhunt for suspects who allegedly committed the gruesome act. According to Captain Stephen Thakeng, the 21-year-old was at her rented room in Meloding when 10 known men, including her boyfriend, entered carrying knives. Thakeng said at about 10pm, she was attacked by the gangsters, who allegedly took turns raping her on two days. ALSO READ: JAILED FOR KILLING LOVER AND NYATSI! “They took turns in raping her, and came back the following day at 8pm. The victim was then gang-raped again,” Thakeng said in a statement. He said that a case of rape was registered for further investigation at Lejweleputswa cop shop. “On 8 February, members of Welkom public order policing reaction team and crime intelligence followed up on information during a tracing operation. “Three suspects, aged 25, 29 and 30, were arrested for rape,” Thakeng said, adding that they will appear in the Virginia Magistrates Court soon. He said cops were working hard to find the other suspects.